<span id="freeTextContainer8343082124154879062">It&apos;s an idyllic afternoon in the English countryside; the bliss and quiet is is broken by the desperate pleas of a child in distress. Our protagonist rushes to the scene, as do a number of other people. A hot air balloon has lost its tether and a stricken child is frozen in fright as the balloon begins to ascend. Each of the people that have arrived grab hold of a rope to try hold the balloon down; then there&apos;s a strong gust of wind, and one by one the would-be-rescuers let go... all but one of </span>
  <span id="freeText8343082124154879062" style="display:none">It's an idyllic afternoon in the English countryside; the bliss and quiet is is broken by the desperate pleas of a child in distress. Our protagonist rushes to the scene, as do a number of other people. A hot air balloon has lost its tether and a stricken child is frozen in fright as the balloon begins to ascend. Each of the people that have arrived grab hold of a rope to try hold the balloon down; then there's a strong gust of wind, and one by one the would-be-rescuers let go... all but one of them!<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1640890921i/32382274._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br>Another great piece of work by the much lauded Ian McEwan. A very well written suspense driven fictionalised account of a targeted object of desire, by a man with De Clérambault's syndrome (erotomania), where the sufferer absolutely and truly believe that their target is in love with them, and also essentially made the first advances and continues to do so. The highly gripping, yet almost understated dramatic opening scene (see paragraph above) that kicked off the antagonist's erotomaniac fixation, was such an innovative and absorbing introduction to the characters and the book itself. 8 out of 12<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1640890921i/32382275.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><b>2021 read, 2010 read</b></span>
